orful encounters, but also an inner journey, deep into the human experience and the complexities of living in a post-communist world. With its unique blend of sensitive and suggestive language, The Back of Beyond - Travels with Benjamin is a stylistic gem, rendered in seamless translation and appearing here for the first time in English.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aSingle fathersvFiction. 0aVoyages and travelsvFiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aCzech writers.  alife journey.  aliterary fiction.  aliterature in translation.1 aBryson, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074322740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781951508135?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781951508135423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781951508135/original  a978-3-11-074322-7  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK